      "description": "Offered is a mechanically superlative 1987 Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2, featuring the definitive G50 Getrag five-speed manual transaxle. The numbers-matching atmospheric flat-six exhibits optimal compression across all cylinders, with a dry crankcase and pristine Bosch Motronic fuel injection components. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, utilizing its original torsion bar setup and staggered Fuchs forged alloys for period-correct kinematics. Every gear engagement is crisp with zero synchro hesitation, and the hydraulic clutch take-up is immediate. This example has been preserved in a climate-controlled environment, ensuring no oxidative stress on the chassis or powertrain. A rare opportunity for a collector seeking an analog driving experience with peak mechanical integrity.",
